# Mandatory project standards

All work in this repository **must** follow the canonical documents below. Read the relevant file before writing or changing code — do not guess conventions.

## Coding standards (mandatory)

**`docs/coding-standards.md`**

Vala style, patterns, and the **Checklist for all plans** at the top of that file. Applies to all new and modified Vala code.

## Build rules (mandatory)

**`docs/build-rules.md`**

Build with `ninja -C build` via Meson/Ninja. **Never** call `valac` directly.

## Related docs (mandatory when applicable)

| Document | When |
|----------|------|
| **`docs/code-documentation.md`** | Docblocks, Valadoc markup, API comments |
| **`docs/guide-to-writing-plans.md`** | Implementing from `docs/plans/*` or writing plans |
| **`docs/bug-fix-process.md`** | Bug fixes (debug → understand → propose → approval → apply) |

Plans in `docs/plans/` should reference **`docs/coding-standards.md`** at the top (see checklist section in that file).
